## Test Scenario 2 - Wrong HTTP Method

Each endpoint should reject unsupported methods.

Example:

If endpoint accepts `GET`, test with `POST`.

POST /users/1

Expected behavior:

- API returns `405 Method Not Allowed` or proper rejection
- unsupported action is clearly handled

Assertion example:

pm.test("Status code indicates method rejection", function () {
    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([405, 404]);
});

Why `404` may also appear:

Some systems hide unsupported methods by returning route-not-found.

This still needs documentation.

